WEBVTT

01:04.739 --> 01:08.945
Canter, Connelly, Franklin,

01:09.045 --> 01:12.949
Johnson, Kim, Matthews,

01:13.049 --> 01:17.921
Rodriguez, Flanagan, Devany,

01:18.021 --> 01:21.892
Rauls, Rickson, Samuels,

01:21.992 --> 01:26.260
Simmons, Williams.

03:30.152 --> 03:32.720
It's not your week, Johnny.

03:33.322 --> 03:36.058
Nope, not your week.

04:15.296 --> 04:17.634
John. How's life?

04:17.733 --> 04:20.668
Same shit, different pile.

04:26.008 --> 04:27.077
Everybody down!

04:27.177 --> 04:30.046
On the ground, now!
Get the hell down!

04:30.146 --> 04:32.650
Hands where I can see 'em!

04:33.750 --> 04:35.885
Open the register!

04:44.026 --> 04:46.093
What's the matter, you deaf?

04:52.868 --> 04:55.169
Hey.

04:56.471 --> 04:58.540
I said, "get down."

05:00.276 --> 05:04.647
You know if you shoot me in the stomach,
my chances of surviving go up, right?

05:05.348 --> 05:07.415
Let me help you out.

05:12.287 --> 05:14.724
How 'bout a hole in the chest?

05:14.824 --> 05:18.061
Oh, yeah, yeah. You're right,
you're right. Effective but unsatisfying.

05:18.161 --> 05:22.698
I'll tell you what. Ha.
The brain stem.

05:25.435 --> 05:27.501
Shoot him!

05:29.905 --> 05:31.474
What? Not your style?

05:31.574 --> 05:33.877
I know, I know.
You're right, you're right.

05:33.977 --> 05:37.013
First thing I do, severed brainstem,
you shit your pants.

05:37.113 --> 05:39.315
You too classy for that.
I got it, I got it.

05:39.415 --> 05:41.384
My favorite.

05:41.484 --> 05:44.354
Classic, but with enough splatter
to let 'em know you mean business.

05:44.454 --> 05:45.555
You fuckin' crazy.

05:45.655 --> 05:47.357
Hey, no, no, no.
I'm crazy and impatient.

05:47.457 --> 05:49.259
Come on, come on. Come on, come on.

05:49.359 --> 05:50.450
- Come on!
- Shoot him!

05:50.550 --> 05:52.562
Don't make me do this myself.
Send me home!

05:52.662 --> 05:55.165
- I don't...
- Shoot me! Shoot me!

05:55.265 --> 05:57.131
Shoot...

05:58.934 --> 06:02.736
You either shoot me,
or stop wastin' my time.

06:51.620 --> 06:54.221
Keep the change.

07:39.901 --> 07:41.170
Ha!

07:41.270 --> 07:43.537
Ha! Ha!

08:07.295 --> 08:10.197
I'm not here. Go away.

08:17.806 --> 08:19.876
- Cindy...
- Save it.

08:19.976 --> 08:24.480
Did I not call you last week,
and tell you I was comin'?

08:24.580 --> 08:25.581
Yeah.

08:25.681 --> 08:28.117
Did I also not email you,
just yesterday,

08:28.217 --> 08:30.653
and remind you that I was comin'?

08:30.753 --> 08:32.688
Yeah, a-and...

08:32.789 --> 08:34.323
And?

08:34.424 --> 08:36.259
And...

08:36.359 --> 08:38.294
I got nothin'.
Look, Cindy, I-I'm sorry.

08:38.394 --> 08:41.128
I don't know what happened.

08:42.964 --> 08:45.468
I know what happened.

08:45.568 --> 08:50.237
Look, Cindy, I'm sorry I forgot
to pick you up from the airport.

08:54.643 --> 08:55.912
Well, if you hadn't have forgotten,

08:56.012 --> 08:59.546
how would I know for sure
that you're my brother?

09:02.326 --> 09:03.976
I'm sorry.

09:04.886 --> 09:07.957
Remember that Jamaican restaurant
we went to with that fish?

09:08.057 --> 09:10.693
Oh, yeah. Coley's, I think it was.

09:10.793 --> 09:13.027
Man, that was so good.

09:13.995 --> 09:17.834
No, no, I had enough
to drink at the wedding.

09:17.934 --> 09:18.768
How was that?

09:18.868 --> 09:20.737
You know me, always a bridesmaid.

09:20.837 --> 09:24.207
Well, that's not gonna change 'cause you
already married to this darn notebook.

09:24.307 --> 09:25.675
You startin' to look alike.

09:25.775 --> 09:26.909
Give me that.

09:27.009 --> 09:28.745
You know my life's in this book.

09:28.845 --> 09:31.779
That's the problem.

09:35.550 --> 09:37.687
You okay?

09:37.787 --> 09:39.853
I'm fine.

09:41.556 --> 09:44.026
I'm fine.

09:44.126 --> 09:47.061
Are you taking your medicine?

09:50.866 --> 09:53.169
Let me see that.

09:53.269 --> 09:54.870
Come on.

10:13.989 --> 10:15.958
Mints?

10:16.058 --> 10:17.392
Really, John?

10:18.393 --> 10:20.830
Look, look, my prescription ran out,

10:20.930 --> 10:22.732
and I don't like takin'
those things anyway.

10:22.832 --> 10:24.734
It make my head all swimmy.

10:24.834 --> 10:27.570
Besides, you're always complainin' about
the shit that comes outta my mouth,

10:27.670 --> 10:30.272
at least now it's minty fresh.

10:35.944 --> 10:38.581
Nice necklace. Who got you that?

10:38.681 --> 10:41.250
Some jerk, brother.

10:41.350 --> 10:45.688
So tell me, how are the,
slums of Brazil treatin' you?

10:45.788 --> 10:48.458
They're fine.
I'm flying back tomorrow.

10:48.558 --> 10:50.726
And <i>favelas</i> aren't slums, John.

10:50.826 --> 10:52.662
There's a lot of culture there.

10:52.762 --> 10:57.667
Oh, cultural slums. That-that makes
it better, but they're still dangerous.

10:57.767 --> 11:00.934
I regret gettin' you involved
in this in the first place.

11:02.103 --> 11:03.805
I'm fine.

11:07.043 --> 11:08.311
You sure about that?

11:08.411 --> 11:10.480
Yes.

11:10.580 --> 11:13.182
I'm just tired, you know.

11:13.282 --> 11:15.082
Jet lag.

11:46.781 --> 11:49.650
Take care of yourself, Johnny.

13:45.633 --> 13:48.104
Katarina.

13:48.204 --> 13:50.606
We'll never win them
over wearing that.

13:50.706 --> 13:55.211
I won't win them over,
but I won't keel over.

13:55.311 --> 13:58.146
Katarina! Katarina!

14:25.673 --> 14:28.175
Cindy.

14:30.445 --> 14:34.349
She's alive. Call an ambulance, now!

14:55.970 --> 14:58.472
- Mornin', boys.
- Sir.

15:10.551 --> 15:12.853
Betty, honey? Coffee please.

15:13.454 --> 15:17.960
<i>Detectives Santo and Bororo from
Rio police are here to see you.</i>

15:18.060 --> 15:22.429
- Okay. Send them in.
<i>- Got it.</i>

15:26.535 --> 15:28.910
- Yeah.
- Good morning, Vice-Consul.

15:29.010 --> 15:32.408
Detective Thiago Santo,
Rio de Janeiro police.

15:32.508 --> 15:36.345
And this is my partner, Carlo Bororo.

15:36.445 --> 15:38.948
- Please, have a seat.
- Oh, thank you.

15:39.048 --> 15:41.751
So, Detective Thiago,
to what do I owe the pleasure?

15:41.851 --> 15:44.687
Bad news, I'm afraid.

15:44.787 --> 15:47.354
One of yours.

15:48.223 --> 15:50.159
Apparently, she was doing social work

15:50.259 --> 15:53.361
for an American non-profit
in the <i>favelas.</i>

16:01.002 --> 16:03.737
You know her.

16:04.005 --> 16:04.874
Is she...

16:04.974 --> 16:06.242
Alive.

16:06.342 --> 16:08.310
Barely.

16:08.410 --> 16:11.411
She was found in the <i>favela.</i>

16:11.980 --> 16:14.884
Who the hell would do this?

16:14.984 --> 16:19.319
When you work with animals,
you're bound to get bit.

16:40.541 --> 16:42.976
Hello?

16:44.379 --> 16:45.947
What?

16:47.983 --> 16:50.486
When?

16:50.586 --> 16:52.822
What hospital?

16:52.922 --> 16:55.589
I'm on my way.

17:46.715 --> 17:49.376
- Thanks.
- Kuka.

17:49.978 --> 17:52.679
You heard about Cindy, yeah?

17:53.548 --> 17:56.650
You don't know anything
about that, do you?

17:58.753 --> 18:01.354
That's what I thought.

18:10.499 --> 18:12.334
You think they all lie.

18:12.434 --> 18:14.902
If the shoe fits on the other foot.

18:41.179 --> 18:42.279
These two go with me.

18:44.333 --> 18:45.367
Hey!

18:45.655 --> 18:47.419
Leave them alone.

18:48.437 --> 18:50.937
They did nothing!

18:53.242 --> 18:54.973
Of course.

18:55.875 --> 18:57.778
They're innocent lambs.

19:07.778 --> 19:10.031
Officer Da Silva.

19:10.331 --> 19:12.760
So glad you could join us.

19:12.860 --> 19:14.061
What?

19:15.457 --> 19:19.066
This is your favela. Your assignment.

19:20.401 --> 19:24.039
The same <i>favela</i> where an American
social worker, Cindy Chapman,

19:24.139 --> 19:26.408
was almost killed a few days ago?

19:26.508 --> 19:28.644
Do you have any witnesses?

19:28.744 --> 19:30.412
Any suspects?

19:30.512 --> 19:33.046
Any leads at all?

19:39.120 --> 19:41.088
Soda.

19:45.376 --> 19:46.509
Very useful.

19:48.395 --> 19:49.798
You're right.

19:49.898 --> 19:53.769
It's not gonna work.
The soda is too warm!

19:53.869 --> 19:56.837
We need ice.

19:57.177 --> 19:58.707
Paulo, get some ice.

20:13.721 --> 20:18.227
The department gave your
gentle approach a chance.

20:18.327 --> 20:21.263
One half-dead American later...

20:21.363 --> 20:24.030
It's time to do it my way.

20:44.318 --> 20:47.287
You made a lot of progress.

20:57.865 --> 21:01.100
Let's avoid a nasty scene here.

21:09.110 --> 21:11.913
I'll make you a deal.

21:12.013 --> 21:14.516
Your best fighter...

21:14.616 --> 21:17.550
against mine.

21:20.221 --> 21:24.426
If we win, we live to
fight another day.

21:24.526 --> 21:27.093
But if we win?

21:29.930 --> 21:34.535
We give you back all your stuff,
we let everyone go...

21:35.236 --> 21:37.770
and we never come back.

21:41.575 --> 21:43.876
A deal.

22:03.671 --> 22:05.546
Hey, man. Come over here.

22:09.485 --> 22:11.190
Don't be scared. Come here.

22:19.179 --> 22:20.967
Thiago, he's good.

22:23.840 --> 22:27.812
But let's see how big a man you
are when our back aren't turned.

22:29.792 --> 22:32.272
No matter what happens to me...

22:33.305 --> 22:35.433
this man is not to be arrested.

22:38.025 --> 22:39.371
Let's do this.

22:53.177 --> 22:54.194
Watch this.

23:10.554 --> 23:12.472
That all you got?

23:40.694 --> 23:43.398
So...

23:43.498 --> 23:45.133
We'll come back

23:45.233 --> 23:47.869
as often as necessary

23:47.969 --> 23:52.538
until we get whoever
attacked the American!

23:57.845 --> 24:00.148
And you.

24:00.248 --> 24:04.183
Don't forget whose side you're on.

24:10.958 --> 24:13.192
Thiago!

24:14.495 --> 24:16.796
I brought the ice!

24:55.903 --> 24:57.205
Manny.

24:57.305 --> 24:59.241
John.

24:59.341 --> 25:01.276
Nice suit.

25:01.376 --> 25:03.810
I see you stopped working out.

25:10.250 --> 25:11.853
Good seein' you, pal,

25:11.953 --> 25:14.990
under the circumstances.

25:15.090 --> 25:16.858
Wanna get something to eat?
You hungry?

25:16.958 --> 25:20.161
- No, I wanna go see my sister.
- That's what I figured.

25:20.261 --> 25:21.460
Come on.

25:50.391 --> 25:52.561
We've put her into an induced coma,

25:52.661 --> 25:56.629
giving her brain a chance to recover.

26:09.009 --> 26:11.177
John?

26:12.913 --> 26:15.181
John, you okay?

26:18.819 --> 26:20.221
Will she make it?

26:20.321 --> 26:21.957
I wish I could tell you.

26:22.057 --> 26:25.794
Given the extent of her wounds,
it's a miracle she made it this far.

26:25.894 --> 26:27.362
Hey, come on in.

26:27.462 --> 26:30.632
John, this is Detective Thiago.

26:30.732 --> 26:33.501
He's in charge of
investigating Cindy's case.

26:33.601 --> 26:37.438
I'm so sorry about
your sister, Mr. Chapman.

26:38.773 --> 26:43.244
The crime in the <i>favela</i> is very
terrible, especially recently.

26:43.344 --> 26:47.248
My men and I will do everything in
our power to find whoever did this.

26:47.348 --> 26:49.984
She was volunteering.
Why would someone attack her?

26:50.084 --> 26:51.713
The <i>favelados</i> see an American...

26:51.813 --> 26:53.853
- they see money.
- So, it was a robbery?

26:53.953 --> 26:57.391
Well, she was found without
the wallet, no cash, no jewelry.

26:57.491 --> 26:58.827
So, do you have any leads?

26:58.927 --> 27:02.197
We're questioning several known
criminals from the neighborhood.

27:02.297 --> 27:04.692
- We'll have something.
- Okay, look, it's been a long day,

27:04.792 --> 27:06.324
let's get you back to
the hotel for some rest.

27:06.424 --> 27:08.369
No, no no. I wanna go
where Cindy was found.

27:08.469 --> 27:10.905
With all due respect, Mr. Chapman,

27:11.005 --> 27:15.577
the <i>favela</i> isn't exactly
a tourist destination.

27:15.677 --> 27:18.579
Well, I'm not your regular tourist.

27:20.882 --> 27:22.117
Good, good, good.

27:22.217 --> 27:26.054
Let's, let's go.
Come on, come on, come on.

27:26.154 --> 27:28.988
Thank you, Detective.
We'll see you downstairs.

27:55.583 --> 28:00.321
It's a terrible thing,
all this violence in the <i>favela.</i>

28:00.421 --> 28:05.060
Just a couple of drug dealers
battling each other to...

28:05.160 --> 28:09.428
to sell more drugs to more
addicts in more areas.

28:12.265 --> 28:15.770
If they think you're on
the wrong side, bang.

28:15.870 --> 28:18.871
Right or wrong.

28:22.075 --> 28:24.145
Your sister is in God's hands now.

28:24.245 --> 28:26.214
I will pray for her.

28:26.314 --> 28:28.549
In my experience, all God's good for

28:28.649 --> 28:31.918
is giving people a reason
to kill each other.

28:34.554 --> 28:38.826
Better than killing each
other without a reason, no?

28:38.926 --> 28:40.926
That's for savages.

28:46.600 --> 28:50.169
Next generation, don't be fooled.

29:15.029 --> 29:18.333
Officer Da Silva,

29:18.433 --> 29:21.569
this is John Chapman,
the victim's brother.

29:21.669 --> 29:24.703
He would like to see the crime scene.

29:25.739 --> 29:29.943
Officer Da Silva is in charge
of the security of the <i>favela.</i>

29:31.646 --> 29:33.178
Whoa!

29:55.669 --> 29:57.005
Mr. Chapman,

29:57.105 --> 30:00.008
my sidearm, please.

30:00.108 --> 30:02.408
Are you alright?

30:04.878 --> 30:06.312
Jet lag.

30:09.649 --> 30:11.650
I should be heading back.

30:17.193 --> 30:20.586
Make sure he doesn't
cause any trouble.

30:25.565 --> 30:28.069
Follow me, Mr. Chapman.

30:28.169 --> 30:29.668
Please.

30:36.743 --> 30:38.379
There.

30:38.479 --> 30:41.714
One of the local children
found her just in time.

30:43.283 --> 30:46.487
Not the most secluded place, is it?

30:46.587 --> 30:48.790
Any witnesses?

30:48.890 --> 30:51.492
So far, no.

30:51.592 --> 30:52.794
Yeah, right.

30:52.894 --> 30:55.997
Nobody saw anything?

30:56.097 --> 31:00.268
The <i>favela</i> is a complicated
place, Mr. Chapman.

31:00.368 --> 31:04.472
Nothing complicated about a
slum controlled by drug dealers.

31:04.572 --> 31:06.905
Come with me.

31:19.586 --> 31:21.122
Look there.

31:21.222 --> 31:23.057
You see that clinic?

31:23.157 --> 31:26.861
It treats 250 people a day.

31:26.961 --> 31:29.330
Who do you think pays for that?

31:29.430 --> 31:31.566
I don't know, the government?

31:31.666 --> 31:34.435
The government forgot about
this place a long time ago.

31:34.535 --> 31:38.139
Day care, doctors, teachers.

31:38.239 --> 31:41.042
Drug money pays for all of it.

31:41.142 --> 31:42.844
The drug dealers take
care of the people here,

31:42.944 --> 31:45.780
and in exchange, the people
protect the drug dealers.

31:45.880 --> 31:48.983
Aren't drug dealers just wonderful?

31:49.083 --> 31:54.386
The world is rarely white and black, Mr.
Chapman, especially here in the <i>favela.</i>

32:18.011 --> 32:19.814
- Everything okay?
- Oh, yes.

32:19.914 --> 32:22.515
Time for her medication.

33:25.011 --> 33:26.447
Nurse!

33:26.547 --> 33:28.115
Nurse.

33:28.215 --> 33:30.148
Come back...

33:31.318 --> 33:35.287
Something's wrong.
It's my sister, she's convulsing.

33:42.027 --> 33:45.632
I need a 100 cc bag of norepinephrine
and Dr. Cristo in ICU 3, stat!

33:45.732 --> 33:48.202
How long has she been like this?

33:48.302 --> 33:51.172
Since right after the
nurse put meds in her IV.

33:51.272 --> 33:52.873
You saw someone inject her IV?

33:52.973 --> 33:56.441
Yeah, it was a nurse. She was Asian.

33:58.378 --> 34:00.481
- Who disconnected this?
- No, I-I didn't do that.

34:00.581 --> 34:03.315
I-It was like that when I came here.

34:07.621 --> 34:09.724
Get the IV going.

34:09.824 --> 34:12.860
Lorazepam going. B.P. dropping!

34:12.960 --> 34:14.793
- Get the paddles, stat!
- We're losing her!

34:26.306 --> 34:27.775
- You sure?
- I'm sure.

34:27.875 --> 34:30.110
There are no Asian
nurses on our staff.

34:30.210 --> 34:32.476
I'll talk to him.

34:35.782 --> 34:38.485
So, what'd they find out?
Who was she?

34:38.585 --> 34:41.954
Johnny, they said there's no
Asian nurses on the staff.

34:43.857 --> 34:46.625
You sure you saw her?

34:50.797 --> 34:53.534
- We'll get to the bottom of this.
- No, that's not good enough.

34:53.634 --> 34:56.969
We need a guard here at all
times to make sure she's safe.

35:00.373 --> 35:03.575
I'll have someone
here as of tomorrow.

35:04.711 --> 35:08.246
- Goodnight, gentlemen.
- Goodnight.

35:14.154 --> 35:17.456
- Catch you tomorrow.
- Yeah.

35:53.293 --> 35:55.127
Excuse me.

35:56.329 --> 35:58.130
Excuse me!

36:03.903 --> 36:05.439
Excuse me.

36:05.539 --> 36:08.275
Excuse me, do you speak English?

36:08.375 --> 36:10.344
Excuse me.

36:10.444 --> 36:13.679
Do you know this woman? Have you...

36:17.584 --> 36:20.452
Where'd you get that necklace?

36:21.454 --> 36:23.457
Necklace.

36:23.557 --> 36:26.024
Where did you get the necklace?

37:24.851 --> 37:27.288
Where did you get the necklace?

37:27.388 --> 37:28.289
Where...

37:28.389 --> 37:29.323
did you get...

37:29.423 --> 37:30.724
the necklace?

37:30.824 --> 37:34.028
Stop! Let him go!

37:34.128 --> 37:38.132
He's wearing Cindy's necklace.

37:38.232 --> 37:40.465
Now!

37:45.705 --> 37:48.607
What the hell are you doing?

37:49.976 --> 37:52.912
He's got on Cindy's necklace.

37:53.282 --> 37:54.438
Cindy's brother.

37:54.715 --> 37:56.050
This is Kuka.

37:56.150 --> 37:58.486
Cindy used to work with his sister,

37:58.586 --> 38:01.522
and she was killed a few days ago.

38:01.622 --> 38:04.724
Cindy gave him the
necklace as a gift.

38:12.398 --> 38:13.701
Maria.

38:13.801 --> 38:16.268
My sister.

38:18.938 --> 38:21.308
I'm sorry.

38:21.408 --> 38:24.109
My condolences.

38:39.560 --> 38:43.664
He says he wants to show
you something that he has.

38:43.764 --> 38:45.697
Let's go.

38:50.837 --> 38:53.738
I'm sorry.

39:05.886 --> 39:09.590
The pages were already
torn out when he found it.

39:09.690 --> 39:11.992
This is definitely Cindy's.

39:12.092 --> 39:14.795
Practically her whole
life was in this thing.

39:14.895 --> 39:16.797
Oh. No, no, no.

39:16.897 --> 39:19.266
You keep it.
She wanted you to have it.

39:19.366 --> 39:21.499
It's the least I can do.

39:25.104 --> 39:27.138
Thank you.

39:35.048 --> 39:37.885
So, what happened to Kuka's sister?

39:37.985 --> 39:39.286
We don't know.

39:39.386 --> 39:41.522
Her body hasn't been found.

39:41.622 --> 39:45.993
There have been a string of similar
occurrences all over town.

39:46.093 --> 39:48.362
All <i>favela</i> kids.

39:48.462 --> 39:51.599
Child prostitutes, mostly.

39:51.699 --> 39:55.069
So, if you haven't found the bodies,
how do you know they're dead?

39:55.169 --> 39:57.605
Around here,
when prostitutes disappear,

39:57.705 --> 40:00.140
there's only two places they end up.

